comments: Johnson (POR) establishes himself in a screening position in Wright's (ATL) path and absorbs the contact.
Capela (ATL) turns into Johnson's (POR) body and initiates contact that affects his follow through.
Capela (ATL) and Eubanks (POR) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
Johnson (POR) steps forward into Young's (ATL) path and initiates leg to leg contact that affects Young's SQBR as he cuts back towards the lane.
Young (ATL) applies a stayed hand to Williams' (POR) side and marginal contact occurs as Williams fades away from the basket.
Hunter (ATL) and Eubanks (POR) briefly engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Williams (POR) cleanly dislodges the ball from Hunter (ATL) during rebounding.

Watford (POR) gathers the loose ball with a jump stop, after which he may establish either foot as his pivot.  He moves his left, establishing his right as his pivot foot, and he maintains his pivot foot as he elevates for his shot attempt.
Hunter (ATL) cleanly blocks Watford's (POR) shot attempt at the basket.
Capela (ATL) maintains legal guarding position in Johnson's (POR) path and he absorbs the contact as Johnson spins away.
Capela (ATL) brings his hand down and makes contact with Eubanks' (POR) arm as he is starting his upward shooting motion.  Additionally, the contact occurs prior to the expiration of the shot clock.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined Eubanks (POR) did not release his shot attempt prior to the expiration of the shot clock.
Watford (POR) places his hand momentarily on Hunter's (ATL) hip before correcting.
Johnson (POR) makes clean contact with the ball and with the part of Young's (ATL) hand that is on the ball as he defends Young on the perimeter.
Johnson (POR) brushes Young's (ATL) arm and marginal contact occurs as Young raises his arms on the perimeter.
Atlanta signals for, and is granted, a timeout prior to any contact involving Johnson (POR) and Young (ATL).
Watford (POR) brings his hand forward towards Hunter's (ATL) side and marginal contact occurs at the start of the drive.
Watford (POR) applies a stayed hand to Hunter's (ATL) body and marginal contact occurs after Hunter has released his shot.
Huerter (ATL) moves slightly forward towards Williams' (POR) path and marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Watford (POR) places his hand to Young's (ATL) side  and  marginal contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Capela (ATL) and Watford (POR) briefly engage and disengage during rebounding.
Hunter (ATL) places his hands to Johnson's (POR) front and marginal contact occurs after Johnson has released the ball to pass.

Capela's (ATL) forearm makes some contact with the side of Hart's (POR) head as he secures the rebound.   Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Capela (ATL) jumps towards Hart (POR) and marginal contact occurs with Hart's slightly extended leg during his shot attempt near the rim.
Hunter (ATL) avoids making contact with Watford's (POR) head as he defends the shot near the rim.
Watford (POR) places his hand to Capela's (ATL) backside and slides his hand off as they pursue the loose ball.
Eubanks (POR) places his hands around Capela's (ATL) waist as he releases his pass and marginal contact occurs.
Williams (POR) makes contact with Wright's (ATL) arm during his drive in transition. After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that a clear path foul would be assessed.
Johnson (POR) and Young (ATL) briefly engage and disengage with one another prior to the inbound pass.
Johnson (POR) commits a take foul on Young (ATL).
